OL,3,CThe government doesn't want to change
OL,4,Cthe law on whole life terms - here's
OL,5,Cwhy
OL,7,FITV News' Deputy Political Editor
OL,8,FAnushka Asthana looks at the debate
OL,9,Fthat has continued over whether there
OL,10,Fshould be a change in the law so that
OL,11,Funder 18s who commit such atrocities
OL,12,Fcan receive whole-life sentences
OL,14,FThe murder of three little girls at a
OL,15,FTaylor Swift themed dance class in
OL,16,FSouthport is shocking, distressing,
OL,17,Fsickening and extreme. That is why it
OL,18,Fis understandable that Axel
OL,19,FRudakubana's heinous crime - and
OL,20,Fsentencing - has led to an outcry.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/13
