OL,3,CThe government doesn't want to change
OL,4,Cthe law on whole life terms - here's
OL,5,Cwhy
OL,7,FThe judge gave Rudakubana a life
OL,8,Fsentence, but said he must be jailed
OL,9,Ffor a minimum of 52 years before
OL,10,Fbecoming eligible for parole.
OL,12,FWhy - people ask? Why should the man
OL,13,Fwho cruelly took the lives of seven
OL,14,Fyear old Elsie Dot Stancombe and Bebe
OL,15,FKing, and Alice da Silva Aguiar who
OL,16,Fwas nine, and who horrified so many
OL,17,Fothers, ever get out of jail?
OL,19,FIn truth, he may never be released,
OL,20,Fbut he does have the right to seek
OL,21,Fparole from 2077.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/13
