OL,3,CThe government doesn't want to change
OL,4,Cthe law on whole life terms - here's
OL,5,Cwhy
OL,7,FSources point to international law,
OL,8,Farguing that it would breach the UN
OL,9,FConvention on the Rights of a Child.
OL,10,FIt states that: "neither capital
OL,11,Fpunishment nor life imprisonment
OL,12,Fwithout possibility of release shall
OL,13,Fbe imposed for offences committed by
OL,14,Fpersons beloe eighteen years of age".
OL,16,FThey say that ties the Government's
OL,17,Fhands - although they hope Rudakubana
OL,18,Fwill spend his entire life in jail,
OL,19,Fstressing that the Parole board could
OL,20,Feasily say no in 2077 if he still
OL,21,Fremains a threat.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/13
