OL,3,CThe government doesn't want to change
OL,4,Cthe law on whole life terms - here's
OL,5,Cwhy
OL,7,FYes, he would be challenged with a
OL,8,Fjudicial review that would likely cite
OL,9,Fthe UN Convention, and the European
OL,10,FConvention on Human Rights, but even
OL,11,Fif he lost that, there are ways
OL,12,Fforward.
OL,14,FIn fact, I know that the previous
OL,15,FGovernment - faced with this type of
OL,16,Fcase - may well have received legal
OL,17,Fadvice that would allow them to at
OL,18,Fleast give it a go. And if they lost?
OL,19,FThey could still force through a
OL,20,Fchange in law - as primary legislation
OL,21,Fultimately trumps international law.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/13
