OL,3,CThe government doesn't want to change
OL,4,Cthe law on whole life terms - here's
OL,5,Cwhy
OL,7,FAs the barrister Isabella Kirwan told
OL,8,Fme: "The UN Convention was ratified by
OL,9,Fthe UK in 1991 but not all provisions
OL,10,Fwere incorporated into domestic law.
OL,11,FAlthough the Government could in
OL,12,Ftheory legislate to change the law,
OL,13,Fthe Government must not breach
OL,14,Finternational law, and such a change
OL,15,Fwould result in huge reputational
OL,16,Fbacklash."
OL,18,FIn fact, the previous Government was
OL,19,Fgoing through a similar process in its
OL,20,Fattempts to circumvent human rights
OL,21,Fchallenges to its Rwanda policy.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/13
