OL,3,CThe government doesn't want to change
OL,4,Cthe law on whole life terms - here's
OL,5,Cwhy
OL,7,FEven on this issue - the fairness of
OL,8,Fwhole life tariffs - the Government
OL,9,Fwas challenged over the case of mass
OL,10,Fmurderer Myra Hindley, and won. As one
OL,11,Fsource put it "international law is a
OL,12,Fliving instrument... It can be
OL,13,Ftested". They said the right of a
OL,14,Fchild perpetrator has to be balanced
OL,15,Fagainst the rights of a child victim.
OL,17,FBut Kirwan continued: "Of course, we
OL,18,Fwould not want the Government to
OL,19,Fbreach international law, and it would
OL,20,Fcertainly result in huge reputational
OL,21,Fbacklash."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/13
