OL,3,CThe government doesn't want to change
OL,4,Cthe law on whole life terms - here's
OL,5,Cwhy
OL,7,FThere are plenty of more liberal
OL,8,FConservative figures who would agree.
OL,9,FThe former Tory Attorney General
OL,10,FDominic Grieve told us that the reason
OL,11,Ffor the law is the belief that
OL,12,Fchildren - unlike adults - can change
OL,13,Fin adulthood. And if Rudakubana fails
OL,14,Fto? He will remain in prison after 52
OL,15,Fyears.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/13
