OL,3,CThe government doesn't want to change
OL,4,Cthe law on whole life terms - here's
OL,5,Cwhy
OL,7,FOthers pointed out that the sentence
OL,8,Fis unique - way bigger than for
OL,9,Fprevious child killers. The boys who
OL,10,Fmurdered 2 year old James Bulger were
OL,11,Fsentenced to a minimum of eight years
OL,12,Fbefore becoming eligible for parole.
OL,14,FSo, 52 years is a long time, making
OL,15,Fthe likelihood of Rudakubana dying in
OL,16,Fprison extremely high. And if there is
OL,17,Fa change of law, it won't effect him
OL,18,Fanyway, as a new law can't be applied
OL,19,Fretrospectively.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/13
